    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                <pb facs="nei.n1b.5.2"/>
                <fw type="curatorial">2</fw>
<note>only 1</note>
                
                <opener>
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>5835 Vine Street</addrLine> 
                        <addrLine>Lincoln, Nebraska 68505</addrLine> 
                    </address>
                    <dateline>May 8, 1973</dateline>
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>Mr. Albert Husted</addrLine> 
                        <addrLine>220 W. 93rd Street</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>New York, N.Y. 10025</addrLine> 
                    </address>
                    
                    <salute>Dear Mr. Husted:</salute>
                </opener>
                
                <p>I have been reviewing my tangle of mail, and I am afraid I did not reply to your letter of March 11,
                1973. Certainly I intended to reply, for I was pleased with your proposition that you come here
                during the summer and do some photographing.</p> 
                <p>If I did not answer you, I beg you to pardon me on the grounds that I have been helping in the
                recording of my work by the United Artists. We spent eight weeks at the job and it nearly demolished
                me. I realize that this is not an excuse but it is an explanation.</p> 
                <p>If you are still interested, please write me again and I will try to be more prompt.</p> 
                <p>The first album is to be issued in July, and I understand there will be number of them.</p> 
                
                <closer>
                    <salute>With all kind thoughts, sincerely,</salute>
                    <signed>John G. Neihardt </signed>

                
                <note type="authorial">JGN:nh</note>
                   </closer>             
            </div1>
            
        </body>
        
